The paper deals with the problem of learning causal relationships from relational data, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of relational conditional independence (RCI) oracle, which is a concept in databases (cs.DB) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for conducting conditional independence tests against relational data, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
